modules.description: This module provides functions to evaluate string inputs and manage a list of printers. It works with string lists and boolean outcomes, allowing dynamic installation of printer names and evaluation of string expressions with optional output printing. Concrete use cases include scripting interfaces where printer configurations are dynamically updated and evaluated at runtime.

This module handles parsing, formatting, and manipulation of MAC addresses. It supports conversions between string representations (with customizable separators), raw octet strings, and structured MAC address values, including validation and error handling for malformed inputs. Use cases include network configuration tools, packet parsing in low-level networking code, and generating unique or locally-administered MAC addresses.
